('5097', '1', 'Prepare barbecue (high heat). Coarsely grind fennel seeds and coriander seeds in spice grinder.'),
('5097', '2', 'Brush salmon fillets generously with oil. Sprinkle both sides of fillets with salt and pepper, then with spice mixture, pressing to adhere.'),
('5097', '3', 'Grill salmon, covered, until center is just opaque, about 4 minutes per side.'),
('5099', '1', 'Preheat oven to 400F.'),
('5099', '2', 'Place orange slices in single layer in 13x9x2-inch glass baking dish. Top with onion slices.'),
('5099', '3', 'Drizzle with oil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast until onion is brown and tender, about 25 minutes.'),
('5099', '4', 'Remove from oven. Increase oven temperature to 450F.'),
('5099', '5', 'Push orange and onion slices to side of baking dish. Arrange salmon in center of dish. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and 1 1/2 tablespoons dill. Spoon orange and onion slices atop salmon. Roast until salmon is opaque in center, about 8 minutes.'),
('5099', '6', 'Meanwhile, mix orange juice, green onions, lemon juice and remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons dill in small bowl.'),
('5099', '7', 'Transfer salmon to platter. Spoon onion alongside. discard roasted orange slices.'),
('5099', '8', 'Pour orange sauce over fish.'),
('5099', '9', 'Garnish with additional orange slices.'),
('5099', '10', 'per serving: calories, 196. total fat, 10 g. saturated fat, 1 g. cholesterol, 55 mg'),
('5099', '11', 'Bon Appetit'),
('5100', '1', 'In a medium bowl combine the salsa ingredients. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.'),
('5100', '2', 'Prepare the grill for direct cooking over high heat.'),
('5100', '3', 'Season the salmon on both sides with the salt and red pepper flakes and then drizzle with the lime juice and oil.'),
('5100', '4', 'Brush the cooking grates clean. Grill the salmon, flesh side down, over direct high heat, with the lid closed as much as possible, until you can lift the fillets off the grate with tongs without sticking, 6 to 8 minutes. Turn the fillets and cook them to your desired doneness, 2 to 3 minutes for medium rare. Slip a spatula between the skin and the flesh, and transfer the fillets to serving plates.'),
('5100', '5', 'Serve warm with the salsa.'),
('5101', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 50'),
('5101', '2', 'In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook the squash until al dente, about 12 minutes.'),
('5101', '3', 'Meanwhile, combine the 2 tablespoons of oil with the lime and orange juices, garlic, chile and orange and lime zests. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('5101', '4', 'Carefully transfer the squash halves to a large bowl and let cool. Using a fork and starting at 1 end of each piece of squash, scrape up and separate the strands. Pat dry with paper towels.'),
('5101', '5', 'Spread the salmon slices on a rimmed baking sheet.'),
('5101', '6', 'Brush lightly with oil and season with salt and pepper. Roast the salmon for about 3 minutes, or until barely cooked through.'),
('5101', '7', 'In a medium bowl, toss the cucumbers, mint and dressing with the squash strands. Mound the salad on plates, top with the salmon and serve.'),
('5103', '1', 'Break cooked salmon into chunk sized pieces and add to bowl.'),
('5103', '2', 'Combine celery, red onion, capers, lemon juice, olive oil, fresh dill in a separate dish. Gently add the dressing mixture into the bowl of salmon, mixing just enough so all pieces are coated.'),
('5103', '3', 'Add a sprinkling of salt and ground pepper to taste. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to cool and to allow the flavors to blend.'),
('5103', '4', 'Serve with a slice of lemon.For best results, do not over-cook your salmon!'),
('5104', '1', 'Combine marinade ingredients in a bowl. If sugar is an ingredient in the marinade you are using, stir until the sugar is completely dissolved.'),
('5105', '1', '1 Preheat oven to 400F.   2 Blanch the tomatoes by first scoring the ends with a sharp knife, and then plunging them into a pot of simmering salted water for 15-30 seconds. Then put them into ice water for 1 minute.'),
('5105', '2', 'Drain the tomatoes and peel off and discard the skin.'),
('5105', '3', 'Cut the tomatoes into quarters, remove the core and seeds, and dice the flesh.3 In a large bowl combine the tomatoes, tarragon, basil, chives and olive oil.'),
('5105', '4', 'Add salt to taste. In another bowl, whisk together the lemon juice, vinegar, and shallots (the acid in the lemon juice and vinegar will help take the sharp edge off of the shallots). 4 Arrange salmon fillets on an oiled baking sheet without crowding.'),
('5105', '5', 'Drizzle with olive oil and season lightly with salt.'),
('5105', '6', 'Bake until salmon is barely cooked through and lightly browned on the edges, 8-12 minutes, depending on the thickness of the salmon fillets.5 To serve, mix the shallot mixture with the tomato mixture, and spoon a couple tablespoons around each fillet. Sprinkle the salmon with freshly ground black pepper.'),
('5105', '7', 'Serve immediately.'),
('5106', '1', '1 Boilthe macaroni pasta: Bring a pot of water (2 quarts) to a boil.'),
('5106', '2', 'Add 1 Tbspsalt.'),
('5106', '3', 'Add the dry macaroni pasta and cook, uncovered, in a rolling boil for about 10 minutes, or until the macaroni is al dente (slightly firm).'),
('5106', '4', 'Remove from heat, drain, rinse briefly in cold water (macaroni should be still warm after rinsing) and drain again.2'),
('5106', '5', 'Mix salmon and other ingredients in a large bowl: In a large bowl mix the salmon, mayonnaise, mustard, lemon zest, and lemon juice.'),
('5107', '1', '1 In a large bowl, gently mix together the salmon, bread, green onion, garlic, dill, bell pepper, flour, egg, paprika, lemon zest, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Form into 8 patties. each about 1/2 inch thick. 2'),
('5107', '2', 'Heat olive oil over medium high heat in a large skillet. Cook the patties until nicely browned on both sides, about 3-4 minutes per side.'),
('5109', '1', 'Preheat grill.'),
('5109', '2', 'To prepare couscous, heat the olive oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('5109', '3', 'Add shallots and beets. saut 5 minutes or until shallots are tender and just beginning to brown. Stir in couscous. cook 1 minute, stirring frequently.'),
('5109', '4', 'Add water and salt. cover and simmer 8 minutes or until couscous is tender.'),
('5109', '5', 'Remove from heat. stir in spinach. Toss gently until combined and spinach wilts. Keep warm.'),
('5109', '6', 'To prepare sauce, combine orange juice and next 6 ingredients (through red pepper) in a small saucepan, stirring well with a whisk. bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Cook for 1 minute.'),
('5109', '7', 'To prepare fish, brush cut sides of fillets with 1/4 cup sauce. place, skin sides up, on grill rack coated with cooking spray. Grill salmon, skin sides up, 2 minutes. Turn salmon fillets. brush with remaining 1/4 cup sauce. Grill 3 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or desired degree of doneness.'),
('5109', '8', 'Serve with couscous and lime wedges, if desired.Wild Alaskan salmon is in season this time of year, and you can find it in supermarkets and fish markets across the country. Its rich flavor is worth paying a bit more. The ponzu sauce may be made up to a day ahead and refrigerated. Golden beets add sweetness and beautiful color, but don''t stain like red beets. Israeli couscous has lovely pearl-like grains that are much larger than regular couscous. Use regular couscous if you can''t find Israeli.'),
('5113', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 37'),
('5113', '2', 'Spread the tomatillos on a roasting pan along with half of the onion, the 6 whole garlic cloves and the jalapeos. Toss with 2 tablespoons of the oil and season with salt and pepper. Roast for about 35 minutes, until tender.'),
('5113', '3', 'Transfer the vegetables to a blender and puree until smooth.'),
('5113', '4', 'Add the lime juice, chopped cilantro and 2 tablespoons of the honey and pulse to blend. Season the tomatillo salsa with salt and pepper and transfer to a bowl. Rinse out the blender.'),
('5113', '5', 'In a medium saucepan, heat another 2 tablespoons of the oil.'),
('5113', '6', 'Add the chipotle, cumin, chopped garlic and the remaining onion and cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until the onion is softened, about 5 minutes.'),
('5113', '7', 'Add the beans with their liquid and 1/4 cup of water and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.'),
('5113', '8', 'Transfer the black bean mixture to the blender and puree until smooth. Season the sauce with salt.'),
('5113', '9', 'Light a grill or preheat a grill pan. In a small bowl, combine the remaining 2 tablespoons of honey with the ancho chile powder and mustard and season with salt.'),
('5113', '10', 'Brush the salmon with oil and season with salt and pepper. Grill the fish skin side down over moderately high heat until very crisp, about 3 minutes. Cook the fish on the remaining 3 sides just until lightly charred, 3 minutes longer.'),
('5113', '11', 'Brush the salmon with the chile-honey glaze and grill skin side up until lightly caramelized, 2 minutes.'),
('5113', '12', 'Spoon the tomatillo salsa on plates and top with the salmon.'),
('5113', '13', 'Garnish with sour cream and the cilantro sprigs and serve with the black bean sauce.'),
('5114', '1', 'Season the salmon with salt and pepper.'),
('5114', '2', 'Heat the oil in a pan.Sear the salmon on both sides in the pan (about 5 minutes on the skin side followed by 2 minute on the other side).'),
('5114', '3', 'Mix the sour cream, dill, pickle and lemon juice.'),
('5114', '4', 'Place the salmon on a plate and top with the dill sour cream sauce.'),
('5115', '1', 'Combine the sugar, salt, and pepper in a bowl to make the sugar mixture.'),
('5115', '2', 'In another bowl, combine the dill, chervil, parsley, and lemon balm to make the herb mixture.'),
('5115', '3', 'In a third bowl combine all the ingredients for the mustard sauce and stir to mix. Cover the bowl and refrigerate.'),
('5115', '4', 'Place 1 salmon fillet skin side down in a shallow bowl. Sprinkle half of the sugar mixture over the fillet, then half of the herb mixture, the rest of the sugar mixture, and the rest of the herb mixture.'),
('5115', '5', 'Place the second fillet on top of the first, flesh to flesh, and wrap with plastic wrap.'),
('5115', '6', 'Place the wrapped fillets in a shallow pan and weigh them down with something heavy, like a cast iron skillet filled with a couple of bricks. Refrigerate for 24 hours, then flip the fillets, weigh them down, and refrigerate for another 24 hours.'),
('5115', '7', 'Thinly slice the salmon. serve with rye or black bread and the mustard sauce.'),
